      "side": 1,
      "message": "Some naming stuff:\n\nHelper seems a little vague here for a pretty narrow interface. Consumer? Target? Renderer?\n\nsend*ToGpu() -\u003e draw*()?\n\nAlso, wondering about alternatives to the interface inheritance model. If there was only one method I\u0027d probably prefer a model where sendToGpu() takes a std::function\u003c\u003e and have GrGLGpu... pass a lambda. If it there were six functions then that wouldn\u0027t scale well and maybe an inheritance or function-local class in GrGLGpu::draw() would make more sense. Two functions feels like gray-zone. No recommendation or anything. I just want to put that out there and see if Chris or Greg have a reaction. This may be me just getting a weird feeling because we don\u0027t typically use interface inheritance. Another possibility would be making GrMesh::sendToGpu() templated.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 42,
